New ‘LimitedQuantity’ field (boolean) added to inform dangerous goods classified details in limited quantities (LQ). The element MessageRelease changed to mandatory.

Records.Name: Postra

Records.DescriptionEN: Unique identifier for the message. Used in message error handling, preferred to use message counter or other technical unique value (GUID), or datetime with milliseconds. Shipment waybill number should NOT be used.

Records.Name: MessageVersion
Records.DescriptionEN: Allowed values: 1 When message version is upgraded, the previous versions are not compatible with new version. Version upgrade always requires also changes at customer side.

Records.Name: MessageRelease
Records.DescriptionEN: Allowed values: 2 Different releases within same MessageVersion are compatible with each other. New release doesn’t necessarily require changes at customer side.

Records.Name: TestIndicator
Records.DescriptionEN: Allowed value: TRUE. Not used in production messages. Mandatory to use "true" when the message is a test message.

Records.Name: MessageFunctionCode
Records.DescriptionEN: Allowed values: ORIGINAL. Message can be received only once. Posti cannot handle update or cancellation by messages for shipment data. Contact Posti customer service when needed. (CANCEL and REPLACE are not currently in usage)

Records.Name: DangerousGoodsItems
Records.DescriptionEN: Collection of dangerous goods details. Following mandatory and conditional fields are minimum requirements by ADR regulations and law. Consignor is always responsible of correct DG details.

Records.Name: RegulationsCode
Records.DescriptionEN: Dangerous goods regulations code. Allowed values: ADR (= by road)

Records.Name: MainDanger
Records.DescriptionEN: Main danger label number (for explosives classification code)  e.g. 1.4S

Records.Name: SubsidiaryRisk
Records.DescriptionEN: Subsidiary/secondary risk  e.g. 4.2. Mandatory when applicable.

Records.Name: PackingGroup
Records.DescriptionEN: Packing group. Mandatory when applicable. Allowed values: I, II, III

Records.Name: PackingDescription
Records.DescriptionEN: Description of the dangerous goods package (material, type), e.g. steel drum.

Records.Name: TotalQuantity
Records.DescriptionEN: Total amount of dangerous goods. In case boolean ‘LimitedQuantity’ is used, the total quantity of dangerous goods should be gross weight and @unit KGM. Use 3 decimals.

Records.Name: unit
Records.DescriptionEN: Unit for the dangerous goods quantity. Allowed values: KGM (= weight/mass), LTR (= liters)

Records.Name: ProperShippingName
Records.DescriptionEN: Proper shipping name, e.g. ALCOHOLS, N.O.S.

Records.Name: TechnicalDescription
Records.DescriptionEN: Technical description, e.g. Methanoldioxide. Mandatory when applicable. The technical name supplements the proper shipping name (ADR 3.1.2); mainly substances "N.O.S.".

Records.Name: MarinePollutant
Records.DescriptionEN: True if the dangerous goods are marine pollutant and/or environmentally hazardous. Mandatory when applicable. Allowed values: TRUE, FALSE

Records.Name: Provisions
Records.DescriptionEN: Provisions or Additional Special Requirements. Text field to define special information related to the shipment/transport for example: “Carriage in accordance with 1.1.4.2.1”.

Records.Name: Waste
Records.DescriptionEN: True if dangerous goods are classified as waste. Allowed values: TRUE, FALSE

Records.Name: TunnelCode
Records.DescriptionEN: Tunnel restriction code, e.g. C500D or B or D/E. Mandatory when applicable.

Records.Name: Empty
Records.DescriptionEN: True if empty dangerous goods packaging. Allowed values: TRUE, FALSE

Records.Name: LimitedQuantity
Records.DescriptionEN: In case there are full Dangerous Goods details available, but there is a need to “overrule” the regulations and inform dangerous goods in limited quantities (LQ), this filed is used. Such use case can be valid, for example, when transport mode and regulations changes from Sea (IMDG) or Air (IATA/ICAO) to Road (ADR), e.g. Sea and Air require full DG details with a mention of LQ packing, but Road transport requires only LQ gross mass information. Note, that all classified substances mandatory fields are still required within one DangerousGoodsItem loop. Don’t send empty element! If LimitedQuantity = true, inform LQ gross weight in DangerousGoodsItem/TotalQuantity element with unit attribute KGM. Don’t inform the same LQ weight in GoodsItem/LimitedQuantityWeight element.  LimitedQuantiy Boolean and LimitedQuantityWeight elements are exclusionary for each other. Allowed value: TRUE, FALSE

Records.Name: LimitedQuantityWeight
Records.DescriptionEN: Used when dangerous goods are packed in limited quantities and full DG details are not required by ADR regulations. Sum all LQ packed DG gross weights included to one GoodsItem (e.g. one colli, or pallet) and inform the total LQ gross weight here. Amount is always gross weight in kg. Mandatory when applicable. Use 3 decimals.

Records.Name: RoutingCode
Records.DescriptionEN: Routing code, e.g. 2LSE79172+70000000. Mandatory with certain service codes, e.g. Parcel Connect.

Records.Name: Product
Records.DescriptionEN: Product code. See separate Posti product matrix.

Records.Name: Service
Records.DescriptionEN: Additional service code. See separate Posti product matrix.

Records.Name: TrackingNumber
Records.DescriptionEN: Package/colli ID which is printed on package label as barcode. Can be Posti's JJFI code, UPU/S10 or SSCC.

Records.Name: TrackingNumber
Records.DescriptionEN: Other unique ID agreed with Posti and this is used only with separate agreement with Posti.

records.Name: POSTRA_FREIGHT
records.DescriptionEN: XML API for ordering freight deliveries

VersionHistory.Comment: * New schema (MessageRelease = 1). Is compatible to release 0. The element changed to mandatory. * Default encoding is UTF-8 * New ‘LimitedQuantity’ field (boolean) added to inform dangerous goods classified details in limited quantities (LQ). * LimitedQuantityWeight decimals 2 > 3 Supplementings to description texts: * Posti will charge penalty fee for manual correction of missing or erroneous data * ShipmentDate is PickupDate, if PickupDate not sent * @timeEarliest and @timeLatest cannot be the same timestamp value * How LimitedQuantityWeight differ from LimitedQuantity * SSCC codes must be sent with leading zeroes

* Shipment/Totals and GoodsItem/GrossWeight, Volume, LoadingMeter allow max. 3 decimals. * All parties (CONSIGNEE, CONSIGNOR, PICKUP, DELIVERY, PAYER) has Street2 address allowed. *PAYER Name1 is always mandatory. * Namespace added to MIG root element. * DangerousGoods Provisions added
* New schema (MessageRelease = 2) Is compatible to previous releases. *COD is no longer available for FI domestic * Party Account @type ‘VAT’ and TAX_NUMBER added for roles CONSIGNOR and CONSIGNEE

Records.Name: timeEarliest
Records.DescriptionEN: Earliest time when goods can be picked up. Format must be ISO 8601, e.g. 10:00:00+03:00. NOTE! The same time stamp is not allowed in @timeEarliest and @timeLatest fields. There must be at least one minute difference. If time window not available, only one of the timestamps can be sent.

Records.Name: timeLatest
Records.DescriptionEN: Latest time when goods can be picked up. Format must be ISO 8601, e.g. 10:00:00+03:00. NOTE! The same time stamp is not allowed in @timeEarliest and @timeLatest fields. There must be at least one minute difference. If time window not available, only one of the timestamps can be sent.

Records.Name: DeliveryDate
Records.DescriptionEN: Date when Posti is requested to deliver the goods. Date is only suggestive; delivery is performed according to Posti transport terms and conditions. Field is mandatory with certain additional services; see separate Posti codelist for more instructions. Format must be ISO 8601, e.g. 2019-10-17.

Records.Name: timeEarliest
Records.DescriptionEN: Desired earliest time when goods can be delivered. Format must be ISO 8601, e.g. 10:00:00+03:00. NOTE! The same time stamp is not allowed in @timeEarliest and @timeLatest fields. There must be at least one minute difference. If time window not available, only one of the timestamps can be sent.

Records.Name: timeLatest
Records.DescriptionEN: Desired latest time when goods can be delivered. Format must be ISO 8601, e.g. 10:00:00+03:00. NOTE! The same time stamp is not allowed in @timeEarliest and @timeLatest fields. There must be at least one minute difference. If time window not available, only one of the timestamps can be sent.

Records.DescriptionEN: Provisions or Additional Special Requirements. Text field to define special information related to the shipment/transport for example: “Carriage in accordance with 1.1.4.2.1”.

Records.Name: Waste
Records.DescriptionEN: True if dangerous goods are classified as waste. Allowed values: TRUE, FALSE

Records.Name: TunnelCode
Records.DescriptionEN: Tunnel restriction code, e.g. C500D or B or D/E. Mandatory when applicable.

Records.Name: Empty
Records.DescriptionEN: True if empty dangerous goods packaging. Allowed values: TRUE, FALSE

Records.Name: LimitedQuantity
Records.DescriptionEN: In case there are full Dangerous Goods details available, but there is a need to “overrule” the regulations and inform dangerous goods in limited quantities (LQ), this filed is used. Such use case can be valid, for example, when transport mode and regulations changes from Sea (IMDG) or Air (IATA/ICAO) to Road (ADR), e.g. Sea and Air require full DG details with a mention of LQ packing, but Road transport requires only LQ gross mass information. Note, that all classified substances mandatory fields are still required within one DangerousGoodsItem loop. Don’t send empty element! If LimitedQuantity = true, inform LQ gross weight in DangerousGoodsItem/TotalQuantity element with unit attribute KGM. Don’t inform the same LQ weight in GoodsItem/LimitedQuantityWeight element.  LimitedQuantiy Boolean and LimitedQuantityWeight elements are exclusionary for each other. Allowed value: TRUE, FALSE

Records.Name: LimitedQuantityWeight
Records.DescriptionEN: Used when dangerous goods are packed in limited quantities and full DG details are not required by ADR regulations. Sum all LQ packed DG gross weights included to one GoodsItem (e.g. one colli, or pallet) and inform the total LQ gross weight here. Amount is always gross weight in kg. Mandatory when applicable. Use 3 decimals.

Records.Name: WasteCode
Records.DescriptionEN: When waste transport in question, waste code has to be given. Code is always 6 digits, e.g. 160103. Certain wastes also require dangerous goods details.

Records.Name: TrackingNumber
Records.DescriptionEN: Package/colli ID which is printed on package label as barcode. Can be SSCC, ANSI, etc. format code, but SSCC is preferred. SSCC codes must be sent with the two leading zeroes, e.g. 20 digits must be sent.

records.Name: POSTRA_PICKUP
records.DescriptionEN: XML based API for ordering pickups for parcel and letter shipments
